## Configuration

Add to your `claude_desktop_config.json` (Claude Desktop) or your MCP client config:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "meok-cra-art14-reporter-mcp": {
      "command": "uvx",
      "args": ["meok-cra-art14-reporter-mcp"]
    }
  }
}
```

Or: `pip install meok-cra-art14-reporter-mcp` then run the `meok-cra-art14-reporter-mcp` command (stdio transport).

## Examples

Once configured, ask your assistant, for example:
- "Use `classify_vulnerability` to …"
- "Use `open_vulnerability_case` to …"
- "Use `generate_enisa_payload` to …"
